no cooking involved.

234
00:13:36.984 --> 00:13:39.420
- Nineteen.
- Wow. 19. huh?

235
00:13:39.444 --> 00:13:40.821
Bye. Mirembe.

236
00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:45.218
Just. before I forget. I
already called Charlie.

237
00:13:45.242 --> 00:13:48.954
- you know. to help with surveillance.
- Wow. Without consulting me?

238
00:13:49.788 --> 00:13:50.789
I was being proactive.

239
00:13:51.373 --> 00:13:55.186
Proactive. Okay. Well. remember.
you have to keep a low profile.

240
00:13:55.210 --> 00:13:56.837
I know. I know.

241
00:14:01.633 --> 00:14:03.260
Okay. How often
does that happen?

242
00:14:04.678 --> 00:14:05.989
It's good.

243
00:14:06.013 --> 00:14:07.615
Have you called Dr. Vickers?

244
00:14:07.639 --> 00:14:09.909
- I've thought about it.
- John.

245
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:12.829
I'll see him at the meeting tomorrow.
I'll talk to him then. Okay?

246
00:14:12.853 --> 00:14:15.230
No. not okay. Call him today.

247
00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:22.070
It's good. Thanks for lunch.

248
00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:28.243
<i>Ruby likes to worry.
and I love her for it.</i>

249
00:14:29.286 --> 00:14:30.495
<i>But I've got work to do.</i>

250
00:14:32.122 --> 00:14:35.185
<i>Right now the best link I have to
finding Olivia is Melanie Matthews.</i>

251
00:14:35.209 --> 00:14:39.213
<i>which is convenient because she
called and said she'd like to meet.</i>

252
00:14:40.881 --> 00:14:42.400
Hi. I'm Melanie.

253
00:14:42.424 --> 00:14:44.027
Hi. Melanie.

254
00:14:44.051 --> 00:14:45.344
I'm an alcoholic.

255
00:14:46.845 --> 00:14:48.865
I haven't been to a
meeting in a long time.

256
00:14:48.889 --> 00:14:54.603
And I mean a long time.
I was 23 years sober.

257
00:14:56.855 --> 00:14:59.358
But as of two weeks ago. I
started drinking like a fish.

258
00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:04.506
But that all ended last night.

259
00:15:04.530 --> 00:15:08.468
'Cause last night I brought a
total stranger into my house.

260
00:15:08.492 --> 00:15:13.038
and that's something I haven't
done since I was in my 20s.

261
00:15:15.040 --> 00:15:19.336
But because I was fucked-up. I
brought a stranger into my home.

262
00:15:24.299 --> 00:15:27.052
I think the reason we
get fucked-up is simple.

263
00:15:28.095 --> 00:15:29.847
- <i>They're lonely.</i>
- We're lonely.

264
00:15:34.893 --> 00:15:36.228
<i>And we're afraid.</i>

265
00:15:39.439 --> 00:15:41.918
And here we live in a world
with millions of people

266
00:15:41.942 --> 00:15:45.237
all with the capacity to love
and be loved. and somehow

267
00:15:47.197 --> 00:15:49.217
<i>we just can't get
our shit together.</i>

268
00:15:49.241 --> 00:15:51.660
<i>And I think it's
because we're afraid.</i>

269
00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:57.433
We've been hurt in the past. and
we don't want to be hurt again.

270
00:15:57.457 --> 00:16:01.295
<i>So... we get fucked-up.</i>

271
00:16:03.005 --> 00:16:04.983
<i>make bad choices</i>

272
00:16:05.007 --> 00:16:07.384
<i>and settle for any kind
of connection we can find.</i>

273
00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:12.139
But you know what
happened last night?

274
00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:16.494
The guy didn't hurt me.
He didn't steal from me.

275
00:16:16.518 --> 00:16:21.273
He didn't even fuck me. even though at
the time I told him I wanted him to.

276
00:16:22.983 --> 00:16:24.109
No. You know what he did?

277
00:16:26.737 --> 00:16:28.530
He took care of me.

278
00:16:30.574 --> 00:16:34.620
He tucked me in
and then he left.

279
00:16:35.412 --> 00:16:38.790
<i>I was technically
working. Still am.</i>

280
00:16:40.042 --> 00:16:42.103
And this morning when I woke up.

281
00:16:42.127 --> 00:16:43.855
I was struck by the possibility

282
00:16:43.879 --> 00:16:47.382
that this man might have been
sent to me by my Higher Power.

283
00:16:49.301 --> 00:16:50.844
Or he's just a decent guy.

284
00:16:53.138 --> 00:16:54.640
Or he's gay.

285
00:16:58.519 --> 00:17:02.773
But. you know. it-it doesn't
matter what he was or is.

286
00:17:04.191 --> 00:17:06.503
What matters is how
he made me feel.

287
00:17:06.527 --> 00:17:11.615
and he made me feel like
I deserve a second chance.

288
00:17:12.241 --> 00:17:14.159
So. thanks.

289
00:17:23.877 --> 00:17:24.962
{\an8}Thanks for coming.

290
00:17:25.587 --> 00:17:26.588
Thanks for asking me.

291
00:17:27.297 --> 00:17:29.383
- You want to talk about Olivia?
- I do.

292
00:17:29.883 --> 00:17:32.779
I'm still hungover. You
wanna get some food?

293
00:17:32.803 --> 00:17:34.239
- Sure.
- Can I get a ride?

294
00:17:34.263 --> 00:17:35.347
- Uh-huh.
- Good.

295
00:17:40.686 --> 00:17:44.541
When I woke up. I dumped all the booze.
so sparkling water is all you get.

296
00:17:44.565 --> 00:17:46.626
- That's fine.
- Yeah. I know.

297
00:17:46.650 --> 00:17:47.860
You can't get drunk.

298
00:17:49.278 --> 00:17:51.697
- You remembered.
- Yeah. that I will never forget.

299
00:17:53.949 --> 00:17:57.303
So. yesterday. were you
following me. John Sugar...

300
00:17:57.327 --> 00:18:01.266
- No. No. complete coincidence.
- Private investigator? No?

301
00:18:01.290 --> 00:18:03.977
I was just following
another lead.

302
00:18:04.001 --> 00:18:05.169
This one.

303
00:18:05.711 --> 00:18:06.813
- Yeah. that's the one.
- Yeah.

304
00:18:06.837 --> 00:18:09.649
Well. if you wanted to talk about
Olivia. you could have just asked.

305
00:18:09.673 --> 00:18:12.277
I'm not sure I would have believed
everything you said last night.

306
00:18:12.301 --> 00:18:14.696
I hate to break it to you.
Drunk. I'm an open book.

307
00:18:14.720 --> 00:18:16.096
Sober. I'm cagey as hell.

308
00:18:16.972 --> 00:18:19.033
You feel the need to be cagey
when it comes to Olivia?

309
00:18:19.057 --> 00:18:20.118
I didn't say that.

310
00:18:20.142 --> 00:18:21.435
Can I ask you a question?

311
00:18:21.977 --> 00:18:24.980
Why was she here almost every night
the week before she disappeared?

312
00:18:25.564 --> 00:18:27.041
What makes you
think she was here?

313
00:18:27.065 --> 00:18:29.026
- I know she was here.
- How do you know?

314
00:18:29.526 --> 00:18:31.796
GPS system in her
car keeps a record.

315
00:18:31.820 --> 00:18:33.590
How do you know she was driving?

316
00:18:33.614 --> 00:18:35.949
How do you know a friend
didn't take her car?

317
00:18:37.284 --> 00:18:38.410
Is that what happened?

318
00:18:43.498 --> 00:18:45.378
I guess this is what you
call being cagey. huh?

319
00:18:49.379 --> 00:18:52.650
Well. I've been through most
of Olivia's social media posts

320
00:18:52.674 --> 00:18:53.735
over the past six months.

321
00:18:53.759 --> 00:18:55.969
And it's mostly
pretty normal stuff.

322
00:18:56.887 --> 00:18:59.473
but it changed when you two started
spending more time together.

323
00:19:00.766 --> 00:19:01.993
You know. her focus. it shifted.

324
00:19:02.017 --> 00:19:04.787
- It turned to women's rights issues.
- What... What's wrong with that?

325
00:19:04.811 --> 00:19:06.313
No. not a... not a thing.

326
00:19:06.897 --> 00:19:09.983
I think she finally found
something she was passionate about.

327
00:19:11.401 --> 00:19:13.713
But two weeks ago. when
she disappeared. well.

328
00:19:13.737 --> 00:19:15.882
her online presence disappeared
also. and that's concerning.

329
00:19:15.906 --> 00:19:18.676
Well. when you're talking about an addict.
there's a reason for a shift in behavior.

330
00:19:18.700 --> 00:19:21.888
She's probably using
again. Look. i-it...

331
00:19:21.912 --> 00:19:23.932
She's probably gonna
walk in here any day now.

332
00:19:23.956 --> 00:19:28.335
just hungover and strung out
and ready to get back to rehab.

333
00:19:29.920 --> 00:19:30.921
That's funny.

334
00:19:31.797 --> 00:19:33.608
Your ex-husband told me the
same thing this morning.

335
00:19:33.632 --> 00:19:35.551
using almost exactly
the same words.

336
00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:40.031
<i>Of course. he did.
Circling the wagons.</i>

337
00:19:40.055 --> 00:19:42.850
Yeah. well. he called me after
you had breakfast with him.

338
00:19:43.934 --> 00:19:47.288
Bernie was a terrible husband. but
he's always been a great friend.

339
00:19:47.312 --> 00:19:48.480
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

340
00:19:50.774 --> 00:19:53.861
- <i>That hair touch. that's her tell.</i>
- Look at this.

341
00:19:54.611 --> 00:19:56.822
I need you to tell me if
you've ever seen this man.

342
00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:02.929
Melanie. if you're in trouble or
if you know Olivia's in trouble.

343
00:20:02.953 --> 00:20:04.997
I can help. Just tell
me what happened.

344
00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:09.435
I've never seen that
man before in my life.

345
00:20:09.459 --> 00:20:11.146
- Why are you doing this?
- Doing what?

346
00:20:11.170 --> 00:20:13.046
This. Your little act. I...

347
00:20:14.131 --> 00:20:16.550
I know you're lying. I
just can't figure out why.

348
00:20:18.218 --> 00:20:19.469
Maybe you're hiding something.

349
00:20:19.970 --> 00:20:21.156
Like what?

350
00:20:21.180 --> 00:20:22.347
Like where she is.

351
00:20:23.891 --> 00:20:25.809
Or where her body can be found.

352
00:20:28.437 --> 00:20:29.414
Get out of my house.

353
00:20:29.438 --> 00:20:34.502
I know you think you're helping her. but
you're doing her more harm than good.

354
00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:36.629
- Okay. get out of my house.
- Let me make this clear.

355
00:20:36.653 --> 00:20:38.739
I will find Olivia.

356
00:20:39.698 --> 00:20:41.158
It's what I do.

357
00:20:41.825 --> 00:20:43.035
I'm very good at it.

358
00:20:47.831 --> 00:20:48.832
Now.

359
00:21:04.139 --> 00:21:05.140
<i>Hey. Charlie.</i>

360
00:21:05.682 --> 00:21:08.578
I think she knows where the girl is.
and she'll take us there tomorrow.

361
00:21:08.602 --> 00:21:10.187
Let's get the van ready. yeah?

362
00:21:10.771 --> 00:21:12.981
I'll see you in the
morning. All right. Bye.

363
00:21:23.825 --> 00:21:26.161
<i>You know. I think that
movies are a conspiracy.</i>

364
00:21:26.703 --> 00:21:27.746
<i>I mean it.</i>

365
00:21:28.372 --> 00:21:32.560
<i>They are actually a conspiracy
because they set you up. Florence.</i>

366
00:21:32.584 --> 00:21:35.629
<i>They set you up from the
time you're a little kid.</i>

367
00:21:36.129 --> 00:21:38.650
<i>They set you up to
believe in everything.</i>

368
00:21:38.674 --> 00:21:44.674
<i>In ideals and strength and
good guys and. of course. love.</i>

369
00:21:46.807 --> 00:21:51.579
<i>But there's no Charles
Boyer in my life. Florence.</i>

370
00:21:51.603 --> 00:21:55.041
<i>I never met Clark Gable. I
never met Humphrey Bogart.</i>

371
00:21:55.065 --> 00:21:56.668
<i>I never... I never
met any of them.</i>

372
00:21:56.692 --> 00:21:57.961
<i>You know who I mean.</i>

373
00:21:57.985 --> 00:22:00.487
<i>I mean. they don't exist.
Florence. That's the truth.</i>

374
00:22:12.875 --> 00:22:14.001
<i>That car again.</i>

375
00:22:15.460 --> 00:22:17.004
<i>Someone keeping an eye on me.</i>

376
00:22:17.504 --> 00:22:19.339
<i>On and off. keeping
their distance.</i>

377
00:22:20.674 --> 00:22:23.635
<i>They're pretty
good. but I see 'em.</i>

378
00:22:38.025 --> 00:22:40.527
Hey! Hey! Hey!

379
00:22:46.241 --> 00:22:47.242
Carl?

380
00:22:48.076 --> 00:22:49.077
Wiley.

381
00:22:50.162 --> 00:22:51.496
Hey. anyone seen Carl?

382
00:22:53.207 --> 00:22:55.751
- Tall guy. Blond hair. Anyone? Carl.
- No.

383
00:22:57.711 --> 00:22:59.755
- Carl!
- Get the hell out of here. man.

384
00:23:06.053 --> 00:23:07.030
<i>We're sorry.</i>

385
00:23:07.054 --> 00:23:08.198
- <i>You have reached a number...</i>
- Shit.

386
00:23:08.222 --> 00:23:10.422
- <i>that has been disconnected.</i>
- Come here. Come here.

387
00:23:10.682 --> 00:23:13.727
In you go. Come on.
Attaboy. Attaboy.

388
00:23:30.077 --> 00:23:31.662
<i>I know. I know.</i>

389
00:23:32.454 --> 00:23:33.580
<i>What do I care?</i>

390
00:23:34.373 --> 00:23:35.874
<i>What business is this of mine?</i>

391
00:23:37.501 --> 00:23:40.671
<i>Yeah. I often ask myself
the same question.</i>

392
00:23:45.801 --> 00:23:46.801
All right.

393
00:24:38.854 --> 00:24:40.105
Goddamn it. Carl.

394
00:24:49.031 --> 00:24:50.383
Who the fuck are you?

395
00:24:50.407 --> 00:24:51.617
What did you give him?

396
00:24:55.662 --> 00:24:56.788
What did you give him?

397
00:24:59.041 --> 00:25:00.417
Fuck off.

398
00:25:06.131 --> 00:25:07.131
Hey!

399
00:25:16.141 --> 00:25:18.018
<i>I don't like hurting people.</i>

400
00:25:20.312 --> 00:25:21.313
<i>I really don't.</i>

401
00:25:33.158 --> 00:25:34.159
I was never here.

402
00:25:37.162 --> 00:25:38.765
<i>But this is what I mean.</i>

403
00:25:38.789 --> 00:25:42.000
<i>A drug overdose.
Happens every day.</i>

404
00:25:43.085 --> 00:25:44.419
<i>Why do I care?</i>

405
00:25:46.421 --> 00:25:51.760
<i>Why do I feel angry? Why
do I feel anything at all?</i>

406
00:26:26.920 --> 00:26:28.297
- Hey.
- Hi.

407
00:26:28.881 --> 00:26:30.632
You're interrupting
my bridge club.

408
00:26:31.800 --> 00:26:34.386
Right. Tuesday
night bridge. Fun.

409
00:26:35.262 --> 00:26:37.639
- All right. Good night. John.
- Can I come in?

410
00:26:38.640 --> 00:26:41.077
Is there something urgent
regarding the Siegel case?

411
00:26:41.101 --> 00:26:44.730
No. No. not really. No. I-I...

412
00:26:48.525 --> 00:26:50.819
- He needs a place to stay.
- John.

413
00:26:54.281 --> 00:26:56.158
This is Mirembe's house.

414
00:26:59.494 --> 00:27:00.996
And Mirembe only has one rule.

415
00:27:01.496 --> 00:27:02.873
- No dogs.
- Yeah.

416
00:27:03.373 --> 00:27:04.374
Okay.

417
00:27:05.375 --> 00:27:07.211
Oh. gray Volkswagen.

418
00:27:08.420 --> 00:27:09.481
What?

419
00:27:09.505 --> 00:27:13.592
Today I was being tailed by a gray VW.
You got any idea who that might be?

420
00:27:14.259 --> 00:27:16.988
Do you think it could be the
Siegels. like. keeping tabs on you?

421
00:27:17.012 --> 00:27:18.972
No. I think it was someone else.

422
00:27:21.683 --> 00:27:23.936
Did you take care of
our friend in the trunk?

423
00:27:28.190 --> 00:27:29.274
Do it.

424
00:27:30.901 --> 00:27:32.528
Come on. Wiley.

425
00:27:33.153 --> 00:27:35.447
Big mistake. They could
have been friends.

426
00:27:45.666 --> 00:27:50.587
He just left. He said he was being tailed.
No. obviously they are watching him.

427
00:28:11.066 --> 00:28:12.317
I'll be a son of a bitch.

428
00:28:16.154 --> 00:28:17.447
<i>So much for body disposal.</i>

429
00:28:19.533 --> 00:28:20.659
<i>Someone beat me to it.</i>

430
00:28:42.848 --> 00:28:43.992
What am I looking at?

431
00:28:44.016 --> 00:28:46.494
Magazines about movies.
Movies I never heard of.

432
00:28:46.518 --> 00:28:49.146
Movies nobody's ever heard of.

433
00:28:51.773 --> 00:28:52.774
What are these?

434
00:28:53.400 --> 00:28:54.711
Letters from his mother. sir.

435
00:28:54.735 --> 00:28:55.819
Yeah. here.

436
00:28:56.862 --> 00:28:57.863
You took this?

437
00:28:59.156 --> 00:29:00.550
What? He already read it.

438
00:29:00.574 --> 00:29:02.719
- Next time. Davy...
- David.

439
00:29:02.743 --> 00:29:07.497
Next time. David. let Kenny
take his pictures. okay?

440
00:29:08.290 --> 00:29:10.292
All right. What
the hell is this?

441
00:29:10.792 --> 00:29:11.604
An invitation.

442
00:29:11.628 --> 00:29:13.980
Yeah. I can see
that. but to what?

443
00:29:14.004 --> 00:29:16.858
I don't know. I googled it.
I... I couldn't find anything.

444
00:29:16.882 --> 00:29:18.985
It doesn't even have a
location. Mr. Siegel.

445
00:29:19.009 --> 00:29:20.969
Just a date and
time. Tomorrow night.

446
00:29:24.056 --> 00:29:25.158
What about the bug?

447
00:29:25.182 --> 00:29:27.476
Nothing. He must have found it.

448
00:29:30.020 --> 00:29:31.498
Listen to me and
learn something.

449
00:29:31.522 --> 00:29:34.066
I think of my life
as an ecosystem.

450
00:29:35.442 --> 00:29:37.295
- You know what that is?
- Yes. I know what an ecosystem is.

451
00:29:37.319 --> 00:29:39.214
Good. then pay attention.
Because in my ecosystem.

452
00:29:39.238 --> 00:29:43.468
there's me. there's my
wife. there's my children.

453
00:29:43.492 --> 00:29:45.118
and there's my
production company.

454
00:29:45.827 --> 00:29:48.890
All I care about
is my ecosystem.

455
00:29:48.914 --> 00:29:52.018
So when a foreign body comes into
it. I go on fucking high alert

456
00:29:52.042 --> 00:29:54.270
and I wonder. "Is this a
positive or a negative force?"

457
00:29:54.294 --> 00:29:59.192
And the only way I can truly answer that
is to truly understand the foreign body.

458
00:29:59.216 --> 00:30:03.029
The last thing we need is him
looking beyond Olivia to anyone else.

459
00:30:03.053 --> 00:30:04.137
like you. David.

460
00:30:05.764 --> 00:30:08.892
So. find out everything you
can about this Mr. John Sugar.

461
00:30:10.185 --> 00:30:11.038
Fuck yeah.

462
00:30:11.062 --> 00:30:13.522
- I want a report by tomorrow evening.
- You got it. Dad.

463
00:30:31.290 --> 00:30:33.417
<i>Clifford Carter
and Carmen Vasquez.</i>

464
00:30:35.377 --> 00:30:39.882
<i>What's the connection to
Olivia? Why can't I see it?</i>

465
00:30:43.635 --> 00:30:45.304
<i>I'm not supposed to
get this involved.</i>

466
00:30:53.353 --> 00:30:55.063
<i>Just observe and report.</i>

467
00:30:57.024 --> 00:30:58.358
<i>Write it down.</i>

468
00:31:00.194 --> 00:31:01.403
<i>That's the real mission.</i>

469
00:31:09.494 --> 00:31:11.038
<i>That's the idea anyways.</i>

470
00:31:16.793 --> 00:31:18.795
<i>That's what Ruby
keeps telling us.</i>

471
00:31:21.173 --> 00:31:22.382
